(or create a pessimistic disposition of a gender or a group of people.)

00:00:05.041 --> 00:00:07.840
(We would like to apologize in advance for any misunderstandings.)

00:00:14.440 --> 00:00:16.440
(Presents)

00:00:19.200 --> 00:00:25.000
(Theory of Love)

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:29.280
Hello, Aoy and Chod.

00:00:30.200 --> 00:00:31.320
I'm Uea.

00:00:32.080 --> 00:00:33.280
I'm 25 years old.

00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:36.920
I'm a librarian at a college library.

00:00:42.080 --> 00:00:43.600
I just got married.

00:00:44.960 --> 00:00:47.960
A time that should be the happiest in a woman's life.

00:00:49.520 --> 00:00:50.560
But for me,

00:00:51.760 --> 00:00:53.480
that happiness didn’t last long.

00:00:54.640 --> 00:00:56.160
He left me too soon.

00:01:00.120 --> 00:01:01.720
"It was as if your time had stopped,"

00:01:02.480 --> 00:01:03.800
"while mine..."

00:01:04.320 --> 00:01:06.040
"kept moving..."

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:07.800
"and moving."

00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:14.199
Why didn’t you turn on the AC when you arrived first?

00:01:14.200 --> 00:01:15.200
How many times have I told you?

00:01:16.560 --> 00:01:17.680
I’ll do it now.

00:01:21.200 --> 00:01:23.720
I remind you every day, and you still forget.

00:01:24.160 --> 00:01:27.280
Look at this. Nothing’s organized.

00:01:28.480 --> 00:01:30.040
What was the point of coming in early?

00:01:33.760 --> 00:01:35.840
I can't breathe. It's boiling hot in here.

00:01:51.840 --> 00:01:53.920
He passed away doing something he loved.

00:01:57.080 --> 00:01:58.120
After his death,

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:00.800
his parents cut me off.

00:02:02.200 --> 00:02:04.640
("What Do I Do With My Life?")

00:02:06.120 --> 00:02:09.400
I don’t know if it’s because of my unstable career,

00:02:10.280 --> 00:02:11.440
or because they were angry

00:02:12.080 --> 00:02:13.800
they didn’t get millions from his life insurance

00:02:14.760 --> 00:02:18.960
since my husband listed me as the sole beneficiary.

00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:41.920
"I will never find another you."

00:02:48.280 --> 00:02:50.160
Uea, I want to return this book.

00:02:52.520 --> 00:02:54.560
Some people have tried to get close to me,

00:02:56.080 --> 00:03:00.280
but it’s like my heart died with my husband.

00:03:01.440 --> 00:03:02.520
How many times do I have to tell you

00:03:03.320 --> 00:03:06.879
to remove the sticky notes before returning a book

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:07.880
so that it doesn't waste my time?

00:03:07.960 --> 00:03:08.960
Come on.

00:03:09.400 --> 00:03:11.720
Aren’t you even going to check what I bookmarked?

00:03:11.960 --> 00:03:13.720
They’re sections I want you to read.

00:03:14.280 --> 00:03:15.280
Here.

00:03:17.800 --> 00:03:18.800
Return it to the box next time.

00:03:19.200 --> 00:03:20.200
Not here.

00:03:21.560 --> 00:03:26.480
(New Books)

00:03:34.720 --> 00:03:37.240
I was consumed by sorrow for almost three months

00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:39.560
until something unexpected happened.

00:03:40.680 --> 00:03:42.640
A guy added me on social media.

00:03:43.560 --> 00:03:46.400
(Tim Teeradol)

00:03:46.680 --> 00:03:50.320
He said he was in my husband’s paramotor group.

00:03:51.160 --> 00:03:52.360
They used to hang out often.

00:03:54.120 --> 00:03:56.640
(Tim Teeradol: Hello. Are you Uea?)

00:04:02.560 --> 00:04:03.840
We chatted for a while.

00:04:05.040 --> 00:04:06.680
Before I knew it, we were talking every day.

00:04:06.760 --> 00:04:07.760
(- Are you free this Saturday? - Why are you asking, Tim?)

00:04:07.840 --> 00:04:08.840
(I know a nice cafe. I want to take you there.)

00:04:09.280 --> 00:04:11.320
At first, we talked about my husband.

00:04:11.880 --> 00:04:14.800
But then we ended up talking for months.

00:04:21.400 --> 00:04:23.280
One day, he asked to meet up.

00:04:23.360 --> 00:04:24.360
(I want to return Jate's stuff to you.)

00:04:36.320 --> 00:04:39.080
I worried if it was too soon

00:04:39.880 --> 00:04:42.200
or if I was moving on too fast.

00:04:43.240 --> 00:04:46.520
I told myself it might mean nothing.

00:04:46.920 --> 00:04:48.080
He was just my husband’s friend.

00:04:53.320 --> 00:04:56.320
But when I met him,

00:05:02.200 --> 00:05:03.520
my heart skipped a beat.

00:05:04.560 --> 00:05:07.040
He reminded me so much of my husband.

00:05:07.800 --> 00:05:10.080
His style, his walk,

00:05:10.760 --> 00:05:11.800
even his smile.

00:05:16.520 --> 00:05:17.520
You must be Uea.

00:05:19.440 --> 00:05:20.440
Yes.

00:05:21.160 --> 00:05:22.680
- Are you Tim? - Yes.

00:05:23.560 --> 00:05:26.560
You’re exactly like what Jate told me.

00:05:28.120 --> 00:05:29.120
What did he say?

00:05:30.280 --> 00:05:33.160
He said you’re pretty and smart.

00:05:34.320 --> 00:05:37.920
He also said he felt dumb around you.

00:05:39.960 --> 00:05:42.280
How do you know I’m smart?

00:05:42.840 --> 00:05:44.280
We just met.

00:05:44.840 --> 00:05:47.480
I can tell just by looking at your face.

00:05:49.720 --> 00:05:51.360
I want to return this to you.

00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:54.080
Jate’s harness.

00:05:54.800 --> 00:05:55.800
I borrowed it a long time ago.

00:05:57.360 --> 00:05:58.360
Thank you.

00:06:03.800 --> 00:06:06.440
I’ve never seen this before.

00:06:07.440 --> 00:06:09.480
He probably just bought it. It was new.

00:06:09.920 --> 00:06:12.160
But I borrowed it first.

00:06:15.080 --> 00:06:17.440
You and Jate were probably close.

00:06:19.240 --> 00:06:22.360
Have we met before?

00:06:23.840 --> 00:06:25.160
Yes, Uea.

00:06:25.560 --> 00:06:27.320
I went to your wedding.

00:06:28.120 --> 00:06:29.440
At a hotel near Asok?

00:06:30.840 --> 00:06:31.880
Yes.

00:06:32.960 --> 00:06:36.680
There were so many guests, I can’t even remember.

00:06:36.960 --> 00:06:38.720
- I'm sorry. - It's fine.

00:06:39.480 --> 00:06:41.760
I was working in the States for some time.

00:06:42.120 --> 00:06:45.600
That was probably when he started dating you,

00:06:46.320 --> 00:06:47.520
so we never crossed paths.

00:06:48.200 --> 00:06:50.720
But now I’m back for good.

00:06:51.920 --> 00:06:53.320
What are you doing these days?

00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:56.560
I’m a creative director for a few TV shows.

00:06:57.640 --> 00:06:58.960
Like Jate was.

00:07:01.080 --> 00:07:03.760
You’re right, but Jate worked on commercials.

00:07:04.080 --> 00:07:05.400
We actually crossed paths before.

00:07:06.640 --> 00:07:09.720
Jate and I were more like flying buddies.

00:07:09.920 --> 00:07:12.440
We went everywhere together.

00:07:13.400 --> 00:07:14.760
While I was listening to him,

00:07:15.480 --> 00:07:17.320
I accidentally thought

00:07:17.880 --> 00:07:19.840
that this was my husband.

00:07:20.920 --> 00:07:22.000
He was still alive.

00:07:22.720 --> 00:07:24.639
And he was gone for a few months.

00:07:24.640 --> 00:07:25.919
He always called and asked me

00:07:25.920 --> 00:07:27.360
- to come up with plans. - Now he’s back,

00:07:28.360 --> 00:07:29.839
sitting right in front of me.

00:07:29.840 --> 00:07:31.600
- You know what I mean? - Yes.

00:07:48.680 --> 00:07:49.960
- Tim. - Yes?

00:07:50.840 --> 00:07:52.320
Do you believe in true love?

00:07:54.920 --> 00:07:57.960
Like soulmates?

00:07:58.840 --> 00:07:59.840
Yes.

00:08:03.680 --> 00:08:06.080
I do. What about you?

00:08:11.600 --> 00:08:13.720
Science says

00:08:15.280 --> 00:08:16.600
true love doesn’t exist.

00:08:18.720 --> 00:08:22.840
We’re only about 72 percent compatible with another person.

00:08:24.560 --> 00:08:26.120
And that’s hard to find.

00:08:31.120 --> 00:08:32.160
But...

00:08:47.120 --> 00:08:48.120
Uea.

00:08:48.720 --> 00:08:50.440
What’s wrong? Why are you crying?

00:08:56.880 --> 00:08:58.400
When Jate first died,

00:09:00.880 --> 00:09:01.920
I thought

00:09:04.720 --> 00:09:07.760
I would never find someone as compatible as him.

00:09:11.640 --> 00:09:12.680
I thought

00:09:14.080 --> 00:09:15.760
I could never love anyone else

00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:20.480
until I met you.

00:09:22.960 --> 00:09:23.960
Uea.

00:09:25.880 --> 00:09:27.520
You scared me.

00:09:30.440 --> 00:09:31.480
I’m also happy

00:09:32.520 --> 00:09:33.520
that I met you.

00:09:37.720 --> 00:09:39.160
Everything was beautiful.

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:42.760
He replaced my husband perfectly.

00:09:43.320 --> 00:09:46.360
Until some unexpected happened again.

00:09:46.920 --> 00:09:48.200
Chiang Mai, please.

00:09:49.320 --> 00:09:51.400
You can go paramotoring in the mountains.

00:09:51.880 --> 00:09:54.960
I’ll visit an old bookstore in town.

00:09:55.560 --> 00:09:56.640
It’s a win-win situation.

00:09:57.240 --> 00:09:58.240
Chiang Mai, please.

00:09:59.360 --> 00:10:02.160
But I’ve flown there so many times before.

00:10:03.000 --> 00:10:06.360
How about this? I’ll visit the bookstore with you.

00:10:07.280 --> 00:10:09.280
I can help carry your stuff

00:10:09.520 --> 00:10:11.600
and be your personal photographer. Sounds good?

00:10:12.360 --> 00:10:14.080
- You said it yourself. - Of course.

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:18.600
Anywhere else you want to go?

00:10:19.400 --> 00:10:20.400
Well...

00:10:21.200 --> 00:10:22.760
- A cafe? - Sure.

00:10:23.280 --> 00:10:24.360
Just pick them.

00:10:24.440 --> 00:10:26.880
- Sure. - We could visit a hundred cafes.

00:10:27.000 --> 00:10:28.320
- Are you serious? - Yes.

00:10:30.320 --> 00:10:33.880
Do you want to go camping in the mountains?

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:35.360
Sounds good.

00:10:39.600 --> 00:10:41.999
- Camping then? - Sure.

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:43.359
Maybe just for one night?

00:10:43.360 --> 00:10:47.200
There’s a discount for two people.

00:10:53.520 --> 00:10:54.640
You can take it.

00:10:56.240 --> 00:11:01.200
Sorry, I told them I’m off today, but they keep calling.

00:11:01.760 --> 00:11:02.760
I’ll take the call.

00:11:23.560 --> 00:11:25.160
Is everything okay? You look stressed.

00:11:26.080 --> 00:11:27.600
It’s nothing.

00:11:27.760 --> 00:11:29.600
Just the usual.

00:11:31.800 --> 00:11:34.680
This one’s cheaper than the other.

00:11:35.200 --> 00:11:37.080
A couple’s package. It's...

00:11:44.720 --> 00:11:47.080
Hey, what did you just do?

00:11:47.920 --> 00:11:48.920
I thought you said you were at the hospital.

00:11:49.800 --> 00:11:50.800
Who's this?

00:11:53.440 --> 00:11:55.320
A mental patient who steals people's boyfriends?

00:11:56.800 --> 00:11:59.880
I’m begging you, please go home. I’ll tell you later.

00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:02.400
No, let’s talk now.

00:12:03.600 --> 00:12:04.680
What is all this about?

00:12:05.240 --> 00:12:06.320
Why did you lie to me?

00:12:07.320 --> 00:12:08.680
You should go now.

00:12:08.840 --> 00:12:12.999
- I’ll explain everything. - No, let’s clear things up now.

00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:14.000
Mom.

00:12:14.040 --> 00:12:15.240
I want to talk to that wench too.

00:12:16.880 --> 00:12:18.360
Why? Cat got your tongue?

00:12:18.720 --> 00:12:20.520
Why weren’t you embarrassed when you did it?

00:12:20.720 --> 00:12:22.720
- Why so quiet now? - Mom, let’s go home.

00:12:23.040 --> 00:12:24.680
Preem, take your mother home.

00:12:24.960 --> 00:12:25.960
No.

00:12:25.961 --> 00:12:27.919
- I’m not leaving until I slap her. - Mom.

00:12:27.920 --> 00:12:29.679
Hey, don't.

00:12:29.680 --> 00:12:30.879
That's enough. Let's go.

00:12:30.880 --> 00:12:32.640
- Preem, get the phone. - Hey.

00:12:32.960 --> 00:12:33.960
I'll call you later, Uea.

00:12:33.961 --> 00:12:36.200
- Let go of me. - Come on.

00:12:36.560 --> 00:12:37.560
- That's enough. - Why?

00:12:37.561 --> 00:12:39.760
Are you really that worried about your mistress?

00:12:40.080 --> 00:12:41.680
How many times have you lied to me?

00:12:42.080 --> 00:12:44.600
- Let go of me. - Stop, you're humiliating me.

00:12:45.160 --> 00:12:46.479
Let go of me.

00:12:46.480 --> 00:12:48.720
Stop it, that's enough.

00:12:51.800 --> 00:12:53.800
Let's get you cleaned up.

00:13:01.400 --> 00:13:04.760
I'll need to charge you for the strawberry drink.

00:13:09.800 --> 00:13:11.999
I'm so sorry.

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:13.999
- Like I said, - Please forgive me.

00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:17.080
this guy is so much like my husband,

00:13:17.640 --> 00:13:19.920
even the way he tries to make it up to me.

00:13:20.480 --> 00:13:21.839
It’s like copy and paste.

00:13:21.840 --> 00:13:23.640
Please forgive me.

00:13:23.880 --> 00:13:24.960
Please.

00:13:25.360 --> 00:13:27.240
I was called a mistress in public

00:13:27.680 --> 00:13:30.720
and had to pay for the drink she poured on me.

00:13:31.240 --> 00:13:32.400
How am I supposed to smile?

00:13:43.960 --> 00:13:45.440
Phare is my ex-wife.

00:13:47.000 --> 00:13:48.480
The kid you saw

00:13:50.240 --> 00:13:51.320
is my daughter.

00:13:54.840 --> 00:13:56.240
We were in love,

00:13:58.200 --> 00:13:59.600
but that was a long time ago.

00:14:02.320 --> 00:14:04.120
I asked for a divorce, but she wouldn’t agree.

00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:06.040
So I had to sue for divorce.

00:14:07.560 --> 00:14:09.320
The case is still ongoing.

00:14:10.600 --> 00:14:13.520
Phare thinks that as long as it isn’t final,

00:14:14.280 --> 00:14:15.960
she’s still my wife.

00:14:16.400 --> 00:14:18.040
That’s why she acted out.

00:14:19.480 --> 00:14:21.080
That's it, Uea.

00:14:23.640 --> 00:14:26.560
Why didn’t you tell me you have a family?

00:14:27.840 --> 00:14:31.400
I didn’t think it mattered for our love.

00:14:33.200 --> 00:14:35.080
If you had known,

00:14:36.800 --> 00:14:37.840
would you not love me?

00:14:39.080 --> 00:14:40.400
But I had a right to know.

00:14:45.960 --> 00:14:47.040
You’re right.

00:14:48.760 --> 00:14:49.760
Fine.

00:14:50.360 --> 00:14:53.440
It’s my fault. I didn’t think it through.

00:14:53.840 --> 00:14:54.840
I’m sorry.

00:14:55.440 --> 00:14:58.000
But I promise, from now on,

00:14:58.800 --> 00:15:00.480
I won’t let Phare come near you again.

00:15:01.600 --> 00:15:03.360
I’ll finalize everything as soon as I can.

00:15:04.680 --> 00:15:06.360
So you can be at peace

00:15:07.120 --> 00:15:08.200
and...

00:15:12.440 --> 00:15:15.240
stop making that face at me.

00:15:17.400 --> 00:15:18.800
Please forgive me.

00:15:23.800 --> 00:15:24.800
My nose fell off.

00:15:33.400 --> 00:15:36.480
When you said you’d finalize the divorce as soon as you can,

00:15:37.320 --> 00:15:39.160
how long will that take? When exactly?

00:15:43.520 --> 00:15:44.640
Honestly,

00:15:45.520 --> 00:15:46.600
I don’t know.

00:15:49.880 --> 00:15:53.200
Phare holds grudges. You saw that yourself.

00:15:55.640 --> 00:15:57.120
When I filed for divorce,

00:15:58.040 --> 00:16:00.040
she sued me back for money.

00:16:02.160 --> 00:16:04.520
She claimed I had to pay her this and that.

00:16:05.440 --> 00:16:07.040
Plus legal fees.

00:16:08.120 --> 00:16:09.640
It’s going to cost a lot.

00:16:10.320 --> 00:16:12.080
I’m saving up.

00:16:13.960 --> 00:16:15.560
How much are we talking about?

00:16:17.400 --> 00:16:18.920
You don’t need to know.

00:16:20.400 --> 00:16:23.600
I don’t want to worry you. Let me carry that burden.

00:16:25.280 --> 00:16:26.320
Just tell me.

00:16:27.240 --> 00:16:28.320
I might be able to help you.

00:16:31.280 --> 00:16:34.160
Just having you by my side makes me happy.

00:16:36.360 --> 00:16:37.480
Tim.

00:16:37.840 --> 00:16:41.440
If my money can help put an end to this,

00:16:42.080 --> 00:16:43.080
I'm willing to help.

00:16:52.320 --> 00:16:53.640
Thank you so much

00:16:54.800 --> 00:16:55.920
for helping me.

00:16:58.320 --> 00:17:00.000
It’s for the sake of our relationship.

00:17:04.560 --> 00:17:05.800
Come here.

00:17:06.240 --> 00:17:07.400
- Thank you, Uea. - No problem.

00:17:16.440 --> 00:17:18.880
I’m really sorry for asking you to come again.

00:17:19.280 --> 00:17:24.240
In an accident case, we must review everything multiple times.

00:17:24.560 --> 00:17:27.800
It takes several months to process the documents.

00:17:29.720 --> 00:17:30.720
It’s fine.

00:17:31.480 --> 00:17:34.120
Should I sign here?

00:17:34.560 --> 00:17:35.560
Yes.

00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:37.200
(Claimant's Statement)

00:17:37.640 --> 00:17:40.640
You’re the beneficiary of this money.

00:17:40.880 --> 00:17:45.960
You’ll receive the insurance payout according to your husband’s policy.

00:17:46.400 --> 00:17:49.400
As for the compensation insurance from the paramotor company,

00:17:49.760 --> 00:17:52.080
we’re expediting the process.

00:17:53.280 --> 00:17:54.280
Thank you.

00:17:55.080 --> 00:17:56.160
Is that all for today?

00:17:56.800 --> 00:17:57.800
Yes.

00:17:58.200 --> 00:18:01.600
If you need help with your financial planning,

00:18:01.920 --> 00:18:03.680
feel free to contact me anytime.

00:18:04.040 --> 00:18:06.280
We’d be more than happy to assist.

00:18:07.160 --> 00:18:10.560
Thank you, but I’ve already done my financial planning.

00:18:12.360 --> 00:18:13.360
All right.

00:18:13.920 --> 00:18:15.880
Let me take care of these documents.

00:18:25.200 --> 00:18:28.440
Life insurance money from a husband

00:18:29.000 --> 00:18:31.080
can help a woman start fresh,

00:18:31.840 --> 00:18:33.640
so she doesn’t have to hold on to the past.

00:18:34.680 --> 00:18:37.199
I’m sure my husband’d agree with me

00:18:37.200 --> 00:18:40.280
giving my new man this money to fight his case,

00:18:41.240 --> 00:18:44.240
so he can cut ties with his painful past as well.

00:18:48.600 --> 00:18:52.080
But our future wasn’t as smooth as I had hoped.

00:19:02.560 --> 00:19:03.560
Hello?

00:19:04.920 --> 00:19:07.440
- Did you transfer the money to me? - Yes.

00:19:09.160 --> 00:19:10.760
For you to fight your case,

00:19:11.240 --> 00:19:13.160
so that hag will leave you alone.

00:19:14.360 --> 00:19:15.600
But it’s too much.

00:19:16.080 --> 00:19:17.480
I can't accept it.

00:19:19.000 --> 00:19:20.440
Let’s just call it even.

00:19:21.280 --> 00:19:23.519
You’ve always paid for our meals

00:19:23.520 --> 00:19:24.840
and dates.

